Which of the following is the correct way to make the variable 'id' read only for
any other class?

Make 'id' private.
//This will not allow others to read or write.

Make 'id' private and provide a public method getId() which will return its value.//true

Make 'id' static and provide a public static method getId() which will return its value.

Make id 'protected'

Explanation
This is a standard way of providing read only access to internal variables.

